author: Gerren Smith
title: Hope High School Tennis: Bobcat tennis players representatives at class 5A state tournament in Little Rock
text: Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 8:48 AM Hope, Ark. Bobcat tennis players Luis Cortes and doubles team Simmons Bamber and Jaime Duenas are representatives for HHS and the 5A South Conference at the class 5A state tennis tournament hosted at Rebsamen Park in Little Rock. The state tennis tournament began on Monday October 19 to conclude on today Oct. 20. Cortes qualified for the state tournament in singles competition with Bamber and Duenas in doubles during the 5A South Conference tournament at Hot Springs Lakeside. HHS tennis teams are coached by Billy Rook.
